. <br>
<br>
No matter, for this is how it was intended. <br>
<br>
The dark magician has obviously traveled a great distance to find this place. Her skin is not the beautiful indigo she admires, but scales that shine with the strange aura of seemingly unnatural magic. The lizard’s satchels are filled with tomes of necromancy, and her black robes are immaculate. <br>
<br>
Young? Yes, but the eyes betray this Cabilis native’s potential. Guards move away as she steps to the door. One leans toward her skull laden head.<br>
<br>
“Why have you forsaken the Tower of Death?”<br>
“Because,” answers the lizard. “The Tower may be ambitious, but I have much to learn.”<br>
<br>
With this, she steps into the hall. Several drow look up. If they are surprised, they give no sign.<br>
<br>
“I am Arkaron of the city of Cabilis,” The voice is deep and rich. Some had been prepared to mock a lisp, but none could be discerned. “I have been sent by the Harbingers of Death in Kunark to study the ways of the Necromancer with Violent Harvest. For a nameless god has given me a vision—the fear of Cazic and the will of the Prince of Hate can do wonders together. For fear and hatred are brothers in war—for each has the ability to fuel the other. I am of the fourteenth rank, and know I can achieve great things amidst such powerful minds.”<br>
<br>
Arkaron bows low to the ground, awaiting instructions….<br>
